This paper deals with approximation algorithms for the traveling salesman path problem, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, graph theory, and linear programming, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the study of optimization problems, which are relevant to cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
